SmControl

Class SmQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • SmControl.SmQueue

  • public class SmQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    This class builds a queue of all the records in one input V0 file. The file may contain only one channel or could have mulitple channels bundled together. The contents of the queue are processed to create V1 - V3 records, complete with their text files ready for writing out to file.

      • parseVFile

        public int parseVFile(java.lang.String dataType)
               throws FormatException,
                      java.lang.NumberFormatException,
                      SmException
        Start with the COSMOS text file in an array of strings. Create a record for each channel in the file and fill the record with the header and data arrays. Let the record object determine how much of the file goes into each channel record. Create an arrayList of all the records contained in the file so they can be processed individually. Keeping them in the list will also facilitate writing out the results either individually or bundled.
        Parameters:
        dataType - the type of file read in (V0, V1, etc.)
        Returns:
        the number of records in the queue
        Throws:
        FormatException - if unable to parse the file due to unexpected formatting
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - if unable to convert text to expected numeric
        SmException - if unable to parse the file, see log file
